// CONTENT:
// Technical Sheet: Fusion Runtime Core v3.0System RequirementsMinimum Specifications (Edge Node)CPU: ARM64 or x86_64 (2 cores)RAM: 512 MBStorage: 100 MB (Runtime + Cache)OS: Linux Kernel 5.10+ (Relies on newer syscalls), Windows 10+, macOS 12+Recommended Specifications (Compute Node)CPU: AMD EPYC or Intel Xeon (16+ cores)RAM: 32 GB+GPU: NVIDIA Ampere/Hopper or AMD RDNA3Network: 10Gbps+ Ethernet or InfiniBandPerformance Metrics(Benchmarked against v2 Nebula and Standard Tokio-based implementations)MetricSupernova v3.0v2 NebulaStandard Async RustRuntime Init Time15ms40ms10msTask Spawn Overhead30ns150ns200nsContext Switch (Native)120nsN/A1.5μsWASM Cold Start80μs2msN/AGPU Kernel Launch2μsN/A15μs (Driver overhead)Max Concurrent Tasks5 Million500k1 MillionSupported StandardsWASM: WebAssembly Core 2.0, WASI Preview 1 & 2.Networking: QUIC (RFC 9000), gRPC (via adapters).Telemetry: OpenTelemetry OTLP 1.0.Security ComplianceMemory Safety: 100% Safe Rust (core), minimal unsafe in FFI boundaries.Isolation: WASM sandbox provides mathematically provable isolation for Tier 2 tasks.Encryption: TLS 1.3 for all distributed node communication.
